 and in English translation.Shirley Kumove's fascinating critical-biographical introduction highlights Margolin's tempestuous and unconventional life. An exceptionally beautiful and gifted woman, Margolin adopted a bohemian and an eccentric lifestyle, and threw herself into both intellectual pursuits and romantic attachments beyond her two marriages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aBilingual booksxEnglischxNeuhebräischxJuden. 0aBilingual books. 0aYiddish poetry. 4aGeneral Interest : Poetry. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aLiterature : Literature. 7aPOETRY / American / General.2bisacsh1 aKumove, Shirley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKumove, Shirley, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791482704423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791482704/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles